## Subscribing

### New Subscription

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Goldenhunter1206/sellfaster_content/main/public/site/images/user-guide/team-administration/billing/image.png)

If you don't have an active subscription:

1. Navigate to the Billing page
1. Select a plan from the plan picker
1. Complete the checkout process
1. Your subscription becomes active immediately

### Checkout Return

After completing checkout, you'll be redirected to a confirmation page showing:

- Checkout status (success, pending, or failed)
- Option to resume incomplete checkouts

## Managing Your Subscription

### Billing Portal

For advanced billing management, use the billing portal:

1. Click **Manage Billing** or **Billing Portal**
1. You'll be redirected to the payment provider's portal
1. From there you can:
   - Update payment methods
   - Cancel your subscription
   - View billing history and invoices
   - Download tax documents

> **Note:** The billing portal button only appears if you are an existing customer.

### Changing Plans

To upgrade or downgrade your plan:

1. Access the billing portal
1. Modify your subscription
1. Changes are processed according to the billing provider's policies

### Canceling

To cancel your subscription:

1. Access the billing portal
1. Cancel your subscription
1. Access continues until the end of the current billing period

## Limitations

### Not Available In-App

The following features require the external billing portal:

- Direct payment method management
- Invoice history and downloads
- Subscription cancellation
- Refund requests

## Troubleshooting

### Can't Access Billing

If you can't access the billing page:

1. Verify you are the owner of the team account
1. Contact your team owner

### Billing Portal Not Working

If you can't access the billing portal:

1. Verify you have an active subscription or past purchase
1. Check that you're the billing account holder
1. Try clearing browser cache and cookies

### Payment Failed

If your payment fails:

1. Access the billing portal
1. Update your payment method
1. Retry the payment
1. Contact your bank if issues persist

